article.description: — Sukhmail Mathon had 16 points and 10 rebounds to lift Boston University to an 80-74 win over Lehigh on Saturday. Walter Whyte also scored 16 points.
article.headline: Mathon carries Boston University past Lehigh 80-74
article.linkText: Mathon carries Boston University past Lehigh 80-74
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- — Sukhmail Mathon had 16 points and 10 rebounds to lift Boston University to an 80-74 win over Lehigh on Saturday. Walter Whyte also scored 16 points. Daman Tate added 13 points for Boston University (16-9, 7-5 Patriot League). Javante McCoy had 11 points and seven rebounds. Boston University scored 45 second-half points, a season high for the team. Evan Taylor scored a career-high 26 points and had seven rebounds for the Mountain Hawks (9-15, 7-5). Nic Lynch scored a season-high 24 points. Jeameril Wilson had 10 points. The Terriers improve to 2-0 against the Mountain Hawks on the season. Boston University defeated Lehigh 80-74 on Jan. 22. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
